## Test Plan

### 1. Docker Image Validation

**Checks**:
- [ ] Dockerfile uses non-root user (vjlive:1000)
- [ ] All capabilities dropped except NET_BIND_SERVICE if needed
- [ ] No privileged mode
- [ ] Security options set (no-new-privileges)
- [ ] Health check defined and correct endpoint
- [ ] Only necessary ports exposed (5000)
- [ ] Multi-stage build not used (single stage for simplicity)
- [ ] Dependencies installed in correct order (system deps before pip)
- [ ] Cache layers optimized (dependencies before source copy)
- [ ] No development dependencies in production image
- [ ] Python version matches pyproject.toml (>=3.9, using 3.11-slim)
- [ ] No debug packages installed (curl removed after healthcheck? Actually curl is needed for healthcheck - verify it's present)

**Test**:
```bash
# Build image and inspect
docker build -f Dockerfile.production -t vjlive3:prod .
docker inspect vjlive3:prod | jq '.[0].Config.User'  # Should be "1000"
docker inspect vjlive3:prod | jq '.[0].HostConfig.CapDrop'  # Should include "ALL"
docker inspect vjlive3:prod | jq '.[0].Config.ExposedPorts'  # Should have 5000/tcp
```

