## Edge Cases & Error Handling

### 1. Missing Secret Files
**Scenario**: Docker secrets not present at `/run/secrets/`  
**Expected**: Application fails fast with clear error message indicating which secret is missing  
**Validation**: Test startup without secrets, verify error message

### 2. Database Connection Failure
**Scenario**: PostgreSQL not running or credentials wrong  
**Expected**: Health check returns 503, application retries with exponential backoff  
**Validation**: Stop database, verify health endpoint returns 503

### 3. Out of Memory
**Scenario**: System under memory pressure  
**Expected**: Docker OOM killer may terminate container; system should have swap or monitoring to alert  
**Validation**: Stress test with memory limit, verify graceful degradation or restart

### 4. Disk Full
**Scenario**: Persistent volume full (logs, database)  
**Expected**: Application logs errors, may become read-only; alerts triggered  
**Validation**: Fill disk to 95%, verify alerts and graceful handling

### 5. Network Partition
**Scenario**: Backend cannot reach Redis or PostgreSQL  
**Expected**: Circuit breaker opens, retries with backoff, health check fails  
**Validation**: Block network with iptables, verify retry logic and health status

### 6. Slow Disk I/O
**Scenario**: Database or Redis on slow storage  
**Expected**: Performance degrades but does not crash; alerts triggered  
**Validation**: Use `tc` to add latency, verify FPS drop and alerts

### 7. Time Synchronization
**Scenario**: System clock drift between containers  
**Expected**: Log timestamps may be inconsistent; NTP recommended  
**Validation**: Check timestamps across containers, verify NTP installed

### 8. Container Restart Loops
**Scenario**: Application crashes on startup repeatedly  
**Expected**: Docker restart policy backs off, logs show error; alerts triggered  
**Validation**: Break application entrypoint, verify restart backoff and logs

